Rostowski Says Poland Plan for 3% 2012 Budget Gap Is ‘Realistic’

-- B y   M o n i k a   R o z l a l
-- 
2011-09-16T17:42:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-16/rostowski-says-poland-plan-for-3-2012-budget-gap-is-realistic-.html
The Polish government’s plan to
trim its  budget deficit  to 3 percent of gross domestic product
next year is “realistic,” Finance Minister Jacek Rostowski
told reporters in Wraclow,  Poland , today.  The government’s 2012 budget may be revised if the economic
situation worsens, Rostowski said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Monika Rozlal in Warsaw at 
 mrozlal@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
